  "why": "The paper provides empirical, statistical patterns and a case-study classification of failure types (e.g., NoAnswer misclassification, irrelevant answers, lack of reasoning) and shows how different metamorphic transformations and guidance criteria concentrate failures (Tables 3–5, Section 5). These constitute partial diagnostic insight linking failures to dataset/recipe-level causes (for example, similarity of KG triples in CQA reducing diversity) and to model capability gaps (e.g., inability to perform logical reasoning). However, the work does not perform deeper diagnostic analysis that links failures to underlying model internals (neuron activations, learned spurious features, or mechanistic causes) or provide evidence tying failures to specific non-robust features or overfitting; diagnostics remain at the level of statistical patterns and example-driven bug types rather than mechanistic root-cause analyses.",
